{"lemma":"سِتَّة","slug":"سِتَّة","root":"س.ت.ت","root_slug":"س-ت-ت","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ت-ت","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سِتَّة","root":"ستت","pos":"N","occurrence_count":7},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["num"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18845","n18849","n18877","n18878","n18879","n18880"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%90%D8%AA%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"num","gloss":"masculine of سِتَّة (sitta, “six”)","tags":["form-of","masculine"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18845","headword_ar":"سَتَّهُ","root":"st","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", accord to rule, and inf. n. app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sat~N","text_ar":"سَتٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He attributed"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imputed to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"charged him with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accused him of, a fault,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~ahu","text_ar":"سَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAbahu","text_ar":"عَابَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA. [The sense in which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EAbh","text_ar":"عابه"},{"kind":"text","text":"is there used is indicated by the context.])"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n18849","headword_ar":"سِتَّةٌ","root":"st","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, S, M) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sit~a","text_ar":"سِتَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, T, S, M, K,) the former masc. and the latter fem., (S,) [signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Six,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] are originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidosapN","text_ar":"سِدْسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, M) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidosN","text_ar":"سِدْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lth, T, S, M, K;) the latter"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":"is changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"d","text_ar":"د"},{"kind":"text","text":"is incorporated into it; (Lth, T, S, M, K;) for the dim, of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sit~apN","text_ar":"سِتَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sudayosapN","text_ar":"سُدَيْسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sit~N","text_ar":"سِتٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sudayosN","text_ar":"سُدَيْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asodaAsN","text_ar":"اَسْدَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lth, T, S.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinodiY sit~apu rijaAlK","text_ar":"عِنْدِى سِتَّةُ رِجَالٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa nisowapK","text_ar":"وَ نِسْوَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have with me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at my abode, six men and women"},{"kind":"text","text":"], i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"three men and three women:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and you may say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinodiY sit~apu rijaAlK wa nisowapN","text_ar":"عِنْدِى سِتَّةُ رِجَالٍ وَ نِسْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"six men, and also women:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner you do in the ease of any number that can be divided so as to apply to two plurals, as six and seven and the higher numbers: but in the case of a number that cannot be divided so as to apply to two plurals, as five and four and three, you put the latter noun in the nom. case only, saying, for ex.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinodiY xamosapu rijaAlK wa nisowapN","text_ar":"عِنْدِى خَمْسَةُ رِجَالٍ وَ نِسْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (ISk, S.) [Respecting a peculiar pronunciation of the people of El-Hijáz, and a case in which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sit~ap","text_ar":"سِتَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is imperfectly decl., see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"valaAvapN","text_ar":"ثَلَاثَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tisoEapF","text_ar":"تِسْعَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sit~apa Ea$ara","text_ar":"سِتَّةَ عَشَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[indecl. in every case, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sixteen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is pronounced by some of the Arabs"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sit~apa Eo$ara","text_ar":"سِتَّةَ عْشَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and [the fem.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sit~a Ea$orapa","text_ar":"سِتَّ عَشْرَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", thus in the dial. of El-Hijáz [and of most of the Arabs], is pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sit~a","text_ar":"سِتَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$irapa","text_ar":"عَشِرَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the dial of Nejd. (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E$r","text_ar":"عشر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sit~umiAy^apK","text_ar":"سِتُّمِايَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Six hundred"},{"kind":"text","text":"] should be written thus, without separating the two words; because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sit~N","text_ar":"سِتٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidosN","text_ar":"سِدْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the union of the two words is to compensate for the incorporation of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"d","text_ar":"د"},{"kind":"text","text":"into the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":". (El-Hareeree, in De Sacy's Anthol. Gramm. Ar., p. 72 of the Arabic text.)"}],"source_refs":["Lth","T","S","M","K"]},{"entry_id":"n18877","headword_ar":"سَتْهٌ","root":"sth","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sutohN","text_ar":"سُتْهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotN","text_ar":"اِسْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n18878","headword_ar":"سِتْهٌ","root":"sth","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotN","text_ar":"اِسْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below, in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n18879","headword_ar":"سَتَهٌ","root":"sth","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotN","text_ar":"اِسْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below, in two places.       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Largeness of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aisot","text_ar":"اِسْت"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n18880","headword_ar":"سَتِهٌ","root":"sth","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"; and its fem., with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asotahu","text_ar":"اَسْتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places: and see what next follows."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}